item.title: PI or delta? And errors with my ::tele command
item.dc:creator: @SnowBoarder7 SnowBoarder7
item.description:
@SnowBoarder7 wrote:

How do I tell if i’m using PI or Delta base?
And with my ::tele command:
public void customCommand(String command) {
actionAmount++;

command.replaceAll(“no-ip”, “imgay”);
command.replaceAll(“servegame”, “imgay”);
command.trim();

if (command.startWith(“tele”) && playerRight >=2) {
int x = Integer.parseInt(cmd[1]);
int y = Integer.parseInt(cmd[2]);
int h = Integer.parseInt(cmd[3]);
if (x == 3200 && y == 3200) {
x = 2667;
y = 2654;
h = 0;
}
p.setCoords(x, y, h);
}

I get errors saying “p”.setCoords that the p is an unknown variable and stuff…

And on a side note, which is more used? Delta or PI?
